parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rust of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust holes in the frame
perforation of the frame rails
corrosion of the spare tire carrier
fractured frame
rusted subframe
and corrosion of the chassis main frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, causing loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The frame is severely rusted
perforated
or broken
causing uneven tire wear
loose or detached parts
and difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ball joints are loose or detached
causing uneven tire wear
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle
and potentially leading to wheel separation or collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to break in two, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The frame is rusted with big holes
the spare tire falls off
the rear shock mount pulls free from the frame
the frame collapses or breaks in two
the vehicle is unable to pass state inspection
the frame is flaking rust and corroding at joints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the frame rust and corrosion issue under the recall can lead to continued safety risks, as the vehicle may still be prone to breaking in two or experiencing other structural failures.
symptoms: The frame is still rusted and corroded after the recall repair
the spare tire falls off
the rear shock mount pulls free from the frame
the frame collapses or breaks in two.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Notification or Inadequate Disclosure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of notification or inadequate disclosure of the frame rust and corrosion issue can lead to vehicle owners being unaware of the safety risks associated with their vehicle, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle owner did not receive a recall notice
the vehicle owner was not aware of the frame rust and corrosion issue
the vehicle owner was told that the recall had expired.
